# Bonsai Heartbeat - Cron Configuration
#
# This file contains example crontab entries for scheduling the Bonsai
# heartbeat dispatcher on Linux/Unix systems.
#
# Installation:
#   1. Edit this file to replace {USER} with your username
#   2. Choose either dev or prod mode (comment out the other)
#   3. Run: crontab -e
#   4. Paste the appropriate line(s) below
#
# Verify installation:
#   crontab -l
#
# View logs:
#   tail -f ~/.bonsai/logs/heartbeat.log

# ── Development Mode ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uses bonsai-dev.db database
# Runs every 5 minutes
*/5 * * * * /Users/{USER}/development/bonsai/webapp/scripts/heartbeat.sh dev

# ── Production Mode ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uses bonsai.db database
# Runs every 5 minutes
# */5 * * * * /Users/{USER}/development/bonsai/webapp/scripts/heartbeat.sh prod

# ── Alternative: Different schedules ──────────────────────────────────
# Run every 10 minutes:
# */10 * * * * /Users/{USER}/development/bonsai/webapp/scripts/heartbeat.sh dev

# Run every hour at minute 0:
# 0 * * * * /Users/{USER}/development/bonsai/webapp/scripts/heartbeat.sh dev

# Run every 30 minutes:
# */30 * * * * /Users/{USER}/development/bonsai/webapp/scripts/heartbeat.sh dev

# ── Notes ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# - Cron does not source your shell profile, so ensure PATH is correct
# - The heartbeat.sh script sets up the environment automatically
# - Lock file prevents concurrent runs if a job takes longer than 5 min
# - Logs are automatically rotated (7 day retention)
